# Semantic Versioning Changelog
# See https://semver.org/

## 2.0.0 (2026-06-16)
### Breaking
- Renamed CLI entry point from `gitops-summary` to `gitops`
- Renamed project in pyproject.toml from `gitops-summary` to `gitops`

### Added
- Model benchmarking workflow (`gitops benchmark`) with tiered evaluation
- Pre-computed default benchmark scores (default_scores.json)
- Benchmark results documentation (docs/benchmark_results.md)
- Scrum standup workflow (`gitops scrum`)

### Changed
- Updated all CLI subcommand descriptions and routing

## 1.2.2 (2026-05-18)
### Fixed
- Updated README with `--no-build-isolation` pip install instructions and UNKNOWN 0.0.0 troubleshooting

## 1.2.1 (2026-05-15)
### Fixed
- Commit range boundary handling in get_commits_for_day; added since/until parameters for precise date windows

## 1.2.0 (2026-05-09)
### Added
- Interactive Bedrock model selection workflow (`gitops-summary model`)
- Model catalog with family-based selection (Claude, Llama, Mistral, Amazon Nova)
- Persistent model configuration saved to `.venv/.bedrock_model_config.json`

### Changed
- Replaced static MODEL_ID import with dynamic load_model_id()
- Improved commit message formatting: added file count tracking and diff truncation visibility
- Updated README with force-reinstall instructions

### Fixed
- Added .kiro to .gitignore

## 1.1.5 (2026-04-09)
### Fixed
- Tuned commit prompt phrase lists: removed false-positive invalid phrases, added new boilerplate prefixes to strip
- Added "Next steps:" section stripping from commit messages
- Restricted invalid-phrase check to first line only in looks_like_commit_message()

## 1.1.4 (2026-04-09)
### Fixed
- Added coerce_commit_message() to convert narrative AI output into commit format
- Improved build_fallback_commit_subject() for deterministic fallback messages
- Enhanced sanitize_commit_response() to skip irrelevant sections

## 1.1.3 (2026-04-09)
### Fixed
- Added build_fallback_commit_message() for deterministic fallback when AI response is unusable
- Added sanitize_commit_response() to strip review/planning boilerplate from AI output

## 1.1.2 (2026-04-09)
### Fixed
- Added retry logic with stricter prompt when Bedrock output doesn't resemble a commit message
- Added looks_like_commit_message() heuristic validation
- Added COMMIT_SYSTEM_PROMPT to enforce commit format

## 1.1.1 (2026-04-05)
### Fixed
- Handle initial commits: detect first commit and adjust prompt phrasing to avoid "updated" language

## 1.1.0 (2026-04-09)
### Added
- PlantUML diagram generation and rendering from repository context (`gitops-summary diagrams`)
- New modules: diagram_prompts.py, diagrams.py, plantuml.py, repo_context.py
- Diagram types: architecture, containers, data_model, ingestion, sequence, component, deployment, class, state, use_case, activity
- Feasibility assessment (normal / best-effort / skipped) based on repo evidence
- PlantUML setup instructions for Ubuntu, Amazon Linux 2, and Windows
- invoke_bedrock_text() for custom prompt invocations
- sanitize_plantuml_response() for extracting PlantUML from model output

## 1.0.2 (2026-03-29)
### Fixed
- Updated README with instructions for installing directly from GitHub using pip VCS URL format

## 1.0.1 (2026-03-26)
### Changed
- Added pre-commit configuration with hooks for Black, isort, Flake8, bandit, codespell, detect-secrets, and prettier
- Reformatted source files to conform to new linting rules

### Fixed
- Cleaned up config.py and prompts.py: removed stale file references from exclusion lists

## 1.0.0 (2026-03-25)
### Added
- Initial release of gitops_summary package
- Git commit message generation from diffs using AWS Bedrock (Claude)
- Weekly development summary generation from commit history
- GitLab epic tracking: setup, status, update, and map workflows
- CLI entry point (`gitops-summary`)
- Interactive commit workflow with staging, review, and optional push
- README with installation and usage instructions
